
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class ResearchGroup {
  -groupId: String
  -name: String
  -department: Department
}

class Department {
  -departmentId: String
  -name: String
}

class Researcher {
  -researcherId: String
  -name: String
  -currentResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class WorkPackage {
  -wpId: String
  -title: String
  -leaderResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Project {
  -projectId: String
  -title: String
  -workPackages: Set<WorkPackage>
}

class Assignment {
  -assignmentId: String
  -researcher: Researcher
  -workPackage: WorkPackage
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : contains
Department "1" -- "0..*" ResearchGroup : contains
Project "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : contains
WorkPackage "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : led by
WorkPackage "0..*" -- "0..*" Assignment : has team members
Researcher "0..*" -- "0..*" Assignment : assigned to
Assignment "1" -- "1" Researcher : belongs to
Assignment "1" -- "1" WorkPackage : belongs to

note right of Assignment
  When a researcher changes groups, all assignments are terminated and re-created.
  When WP leadership changes, assignments are re-recorded for correct service delivery tracking.
end note
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **ResearchGroup** contains **Researchers** (a researcher belongs to exactly one group).
- **Department** contains **ResearchGroups**.
- **Project** contains multiple **WorkPackages**.
- Each **WorkPackage** is led by exactly one **ResearchGroup**.
- A **Researcher** can be assigned to any **WorkPackage**, regardless of which group leads it.
- An **Assignment** links a **Researcher** to a **WorkPackage** with dates.
- The note explains how **service delivery** is tracked via the **Assignment** class when researchers or WP leaders change.

